<TEXT>
jack henry abbott fighting to keep the rewards 
of the writing career he developed in prison with norman mailers 
help said thursday that when he killed a young actor in 1981 he 
caused no financial loss to the widow 
acting as his own attorney in defense against a 17 million 
wrongful death lawsuit abbott said his victim richard adan had 
no more than 500 when he was killed and was being supported 
largely by his wife ricci now 32 
he also has insisted that he killed adan swiftly with a knife 
stab to the heart and therefore mrs adan deserves no payment for 
adans pain and suffering 
following the judges final instructions the jury deliberated 
briefly then was excused until friday 
abbott 46 gained fame from writing in the belly of the 
beast a bestseller composed of letters he sent from prison to 
mailer from 1978 through 1981 
mailer supported abbotts parole that year abbott had been out 
of prison six weeks when he slew adan outside the binibon 
restaurant on manhattans lower east side on july 18 1981 
abbott spent more than three hours in closing arguments thursday 
trying to convince the jury of six that adan 22 was one of 
thousands of young actors of modest talent who had a 
oneinamillion chance of success before he died 
abbott sneered at a pace university economists projections that 
adan might have netted 17 million in his lifetime abbott said the 
projections assumed that adan would have been a movie star of the 
caliber of paul newman 
mrs adans lawyers have proceeded on a theory of adans 
future value abbott said because they have nothing more to 
go on 
as abbott belittled adan he stood at a lectern dangling his 
left hand which has the letters jack tattooed on the four 
fingers 
mrs adan reacted to abbotts argument by laying her head on the 
knee of henry howard her stepfather 
on wednesday abbott reduced mrs adan to tears then said her 
weeping would prejudice the jury against him 
mrs adan i noticed you have a lot of tissues he said as 
he crossexamined mrs adan did you anticipate weeping on the 
stand do you have any children 
no she said 
just you abbott said 
yes she said as she started to weep more loudly 
abbott then demanded a mistrial because of prejudice and 
bias the judge denied the motion 
daniel leonard one of mrs adans lawyers told the jury in a 
12minute summation thursday that the future was all the couple had 
observing the defendants constant references to himself 
leonard told the jury that the case was not about abbott its 
about the promise of a great life about two young peoples future 
together the lawyer said 
abbott who said he has been out of prison a total of 11 months 
since he was 12 is serving 15 years to life for a firstdegree 
manslaughter conviction in adans death 
mrs adan sued him for 10 million for wrongful death and pain 
and suffering her lawyers upped the lawsuit to 17 million after 
testimony by the economist edmund mandell 
while abbott maintains adan endured no pain because the knife 
thrust killed him almost instantly leonard said there was proof 
that richard suffered greatly for 10 or 15 minutes before he 
died 
mailer very visible during abbotts criminal trial has been 
absent from this one he has not been reached for comment 
mrs adans lawyers estimate that abbott has a little more than 
100000 in escrow held by the manhattan sheriff in case of a civil 
judgement in mrs adans favor abbott also has 15000 earned 
from his writings that is being held by the state crime victims 
board 
abbott asked each witness did you read my book at one 
point he even asked judge carol arber she replied that she had 
looked at parts of it 
he attacked mrs adan and her family saying they wanted to 
punish him by insuring that no publisher will deal with him because 
of the legal lien on his finances 
these proceedings have been brought by mrs adan to stop me 
from publishing again abbott said 
