<TEXT>
the financial center of frankfurt is western 
europes most prosperous city followed by brussels venice 
munich and amsterdam a university report says 
the belgian italian dutch and west germany cities led 117 
urban areas ranked by university of reading economics professor 
paul cheshire 
only european community cities with a minimum population of 
300000 were considered and portugal and greece were not included 
because they could not provide adequate figures said cheshire 
to determine the cities rankings cheshire said he looked at 
their per capita gross domestic product unemployment migration 
and other factors 
the three poorest cities in the survey were all in spain 
malaga cordoba and seville 
the results based on figures up to 1988 are to be published in 
the july issue of urban studies an international journal published 
in britain cheshire made a copy of his article available to the 
associated press on wednesday 
the cities that fared best are large have big service sectors 
and are centrally located in europe cheshire said european 
economic integration is of much greater benefit to the more central 
regions of europe than it is to the more peripheral ones 
the rest of the list also was dominated by west german cities 
here are the remaining 25 most prosperous urban areas 
6 strasbourg france 
7 bonn west germany 
8 nice france 
9 stuttgart west germany 
10 florence italy 
11 palma spain 
