<TEXT>
tommy martin is a single womans dream 
hes a mature easygoing bachelor hes a good cook and he even 
does windows 
boy does he do windows 
every day this week martin scales the sheer face of the 
30story gannett co inc headquarters building one of the tallest 
in metropolitan washington dc to scrub its 5000 windows from 
the outside 
the annual spring cleaning takes martin 53 and his buddy 
lucien coleman 62 about three weeks they finished gannetts twin 
usa today building last week and both gleaming towers will be 
washed again this summer and fall 
from his perch on a gently swaying platform only three feet 
wide martin has a breathtaking view of washingtons monuments and 
treeshaded malls across the potomac river the 380foot plunge 
from gannetts rooftop to the busy streets below is an acrophobics 
nightmare but a downward glance doesnt bother martin 
its a good job he says a lot of people look up to you 
martins been a professional window washer for 30 years and hes 
never suffered high anxiety from the time he climbed trees as a 
kid no sweaty palms no churning stomach no dizzy spells he 
doesnt take tranquilizers and sleeps like a baby at night 
he did utter a prayer once when his platform tipped over and he 
took a fourstory free fall until he was caught by the heavy safety 
rope attached to his belt he escaped with only rope burns on his 
hand 
martin is such a relaxed fellow that when one of his platforms 
electrically powered hoist cables stalled leaving him swinging 100 
feet in the air for half an hour he simply laid down until an 
engineer fixed the problem 
it wasnt going anywhere so i took a little nap he said 
martin likes the fresh air and sunshine the pay is good 140 a 
day and the solitude of working at great heights gives him plenty 
of time to think he says 
for entertainment he waves at startled office workers as he 
suddenly drops into view a sort of highrise peeping tommy the 
other day an airliner roared so close to the gannett building on 
its approach to nearby national airport that i could see the 
passengers inside he said 
martin says he can ride up or down the building in 20 minutes 
swabbing windows and aluminum paneling with a sudsy solution of 
household detergent and ammonia and scraping them dry with a 
squeegee 
a lifelong bachelor martin cooks his own dinner when he returns 
home for the evening his favorite is meatloaf and collard greens 
but he offers a warning to any females who might be hunting for a 
husband 
i dont do windows around the house 
</TEXT>
