<TEXT>
the nixon presidential library opening next 
month will become the most complete source of materials about 
president nixon and his life and presidency even though it will 
have no original white house documents a spokesman says 
the white house announced wednesday that president bush will 
attend the library dedication in yorba linda calif on july 19 
almost 16 years after nixon resigned the presidency in the wake of 
the watergate scandals 
former presidents reagan and ford also will attend former 
president carter was invited but said he had another engagement 
nixons assistant john taylor said from the former presidents 
office in new jersey that nixon would be accompanied by former 
first lady pat nixon and members of their family 
only the exhibit portion of the library along with the restored 
home in which nixon was born in 1913 will be immediately opened to 
the public the archival portion containing pre and 
postpresidential nixon papers and copies of white house documents 
is scheduled to open sometime next year 
nixon resigned from office on aug 8 1974 after the house 
judiciary committee had voted to impeach him on grounds that 
included a coverup of white house involvement in a breakin at 
democratic party headquarters in the watergate office building 
both reagan and bush have conferred at times with the former 
president but bushs appearance in yorba linda will mark one of 
the few times since nixons resignation that a president has shared 
a public platform with him 
reagan spoke at a departure ceremony at the white house on oct 
9 1981 as nixon ford and carter left for egypt to represent the 
president at the funeral of slain egyptian president anwar sadat 
nixon has not attended any of the four republican national 
conventions since his resignation 
unlike other presidential libraries the nixon library will be 
operated by the private foundation that raised the money to build 
it the eight others are run by the national archives as the 
reagan library will be after it opens its doors next year in simi 
valley calif 
also unlike the other libraries the nixon library will not 
contain original white house documents they are stored in a 
national archives building in alexandria va where they are being 
processed and made public 
taylor said the library will contain papers from nixons years 
in the house and senate his campaigns and the period since he left 
the white house he said it will also house some of his vice 
presidential papers some were deeded to the government and are in 
a national archives facility in laguna niguel calif 
in addition the nixon aide said preliminary discussions are 
being held about making copies of some 15 million pages of 
presidential documents now in the alexandria archives building 
when the archival level of the library opens in 1991 the 
nixon library and birthplace will be the most complete source of 
materials about president nixon and his life and presidency 
taylor said it will include copies of all critically important 
presidential documents 
the national archives holds about 40 million pages of nixon 
white house documents but taylor said these include a lot of 
christmas cards and life magazine collections of staff members and 
various less important documents 
he said copying would focus initially on the special files of 
the archives nixon project containing work papers of the 
president and key staff members 
we have not even begun to investigate how the copies are going 
to be made said taylor it may even be that technology will 
enable us to transfer the documents to a laser disk at a much 
reduced cost 
jill brett public affairs director of the national archives 
said agency regulations permit people to do copying on their own 
with approved equipment under staff supervision 
congress gave control of nixons presidential papers to the 
archives in 1974 nixon challenged the acts constitutionality but 
it was upheld in 1977 by the supreme court the former president 
also lost a challenge to regulations adopted under the act 
