the situation was far from euphoric but that a tremendous 
change had taken place in the soviet view of the secessionist 
demands of the three baltic states the estonian news agency eta 
reported 
lithuania latvia and estonia were forcibly annexed by the 
soviet union in 1940 and are seeking restored independence 
lithuania most stridently 
ryzhkov favors having lithuania remain part of the soviet union 
under a new treaty granting the republic special status or 
privileges ms dapkus said 
mrs prunskiene did not immediately respond to ryzhkovs plan 
but the presidents of latvia and estonia were both reported on 
wednesday to have repeated their calls for full independence 
on tuesday gorbachev proposed the transformation of the soviet 
union into a looser federation of more independent republics the 
soviet leader is trying to keep together his huge economically 
troubled union of 15 republics with more than 100 nationalities and 
289 million people 
