<TEXT>
the supreme court today allowed the bush 
administration to limit how much welfare aid some needy families 
receive 
by a 54 vote the court said social security benefits paid to 
children must be considered in determining a familys eligibility 
for benefits under the governments aid to families with dependent 
children afdc program 
the decision reversed a federal appeals court ruling in a 
virginia case last year that favored welfare families in a dispute 
over how afdc eligibility is to be determined 
at issue was whether the first 50 in social security benefits 
received by a familys children each month must be taken into 
account when calculating the familys eligibility for afdc benefits 
the richmondbased 4th us circuit court of appeals said no 
today the supreme court said yes 
todays decision is a defeat for the virginia welfare families 
who had successfully challenged the bush administrations 
interpretation of the relevant law 
the disputed welfare law language says participating states are 
to disregard the first 50 of any child support payments 
writing for the court today chief justice william h rehnquist 
said bush administration officials were correct in limiting that 
language to payments from absent parents and not applying it to 
social security benefits received by children 
congress used child support throughout the relevant welfare 
law as a term of art referring exclusively to payments from absent 
parents rehnquist said 
he was joined by justices byron r white sandra day oconnor 
antonin scalia and anthony m kennedy 
justices harry a blackmun william j brennan thurgood 
marshall and john paul stevens dissented 
this crabbed interpretation of the statute is neither 
compelled by its language nor consistent with its purpose 
blackmun wrote and arbitrarily deprives certain families of a 
modest but urgently needed welfare benefit 
justice department lawyers had told the court that the 
50disregard provision enacted in 1974 could cost 44 million 
more each year in afdc benefits if interpreted as the 4th circuit 
court had 
the case is sullivan vs stroop 89535 
</TEXT>
