reducing conventional forces in europe are close to agreement on 
limits for tanks and armored combat vehicles for each military 
bloc diplomats said today 
an accord would push ahead the overall talks and an initial 
agreement might be reached by the end of the year they said 
the eastwest talks are to cut troops and nonnuclear weapons of 
the two military alliances from the atlantic ocean to the ural 
mountains the 16 nato and seven warsaw pact countries are taking 
part 
the breakthrough proposal came from the french and the poles it 
suggests an overall ceiling for each side of 30000 armored combat 
vehicles and 20000 tanks 
french chief delegate francois plaisant said at a news 
