and fair elections under the united nations lead 
the two leaders in nearly 2 hours of meetings and a working 
luncheon at the white house also agreed to forge new ties between 
their commerce ministers to promote investment and defuse trade 
disputes 
bush called thailand one of americas oldest friends and 
closest allies 
what is most remarkable about thailand is that it has combined 
a doubledigit economic growth with the emergence of parliamentary 
democracy said bush 
bush said he and chatichai agreed to keep pressing for a 
comprehensive solution under the united nations auspices to the 
tragic conflict in cambodia 
both nations will continue our diplomatic efforts to end the 
violence and assure genuine selfdetermination through free and 
fair elections under un auspices and in the presence of an 
international peacekeeping force in cambodia bush said 
chatichai speaking in english said our two countries are 
committed more than ever to work together in bringing peace to 
cambodia and to end the suffering of the cambodian people 
bush said the two countries commerce ministers will form a new 
joint usthai committee for commercial cooperation 
chatichai said they were seeking to establish a new framework 
for economic cooperation that would allow us to regularly 
discuss any potential trade issues before they become trade 
disputes 
the united states currently imposes duties on 165 million of 
thai products to pressure the country to stop infringement of us 
patent and intellectual property rights on products ranging from 
computers to hollywood videotapes to pharmaceuticals 
bush expressed profound appreciation for thailands 
providing asylum to indochinese refugees and assured chatichai that 
america will welcome our share of vietnamese refugees 
bush said there is one kind of business we agree we will not 
tolerate and that is narcotics he promised to keep working to 
reduce us demand for drugs 
chatichai said drugs are tearing apart the very fabrics of our 
societies i pledge to you the full support of the thai 
government in the war against drug trafficking 
secretary of state james a baker iii also joined the leaders 
for the talks chatichai was also meeting with leaders of congress 
and addressing the national press club on friday 
thailand boasted the worlds fastest growing economy last year 
burgeoning at nearly an 11 percent rate 
it is a transit point for half the heroin reaching the united 
states from the socalled burmalaosthailand golden triangle 
the united states has applauded asset seizure and anticonspiracy 
measures that chatichais government recently introduced in 
parliament to crack down on drug traffickers 
thailand also bears the burden of 300000 temporary refugees 
from the civil war in neighboring cambodia it has drawn criticism 
from some human rights groups for turning away vietnamese boat 
people 
the pullout of vietnams occupying forces from cambodia has 
eased the immediate threat to thailands own security a senior 
us official said wednesday making this an opportune time to 
press for a diplomatic solution to the strife in cambodia 
the united states and thailand have worked together to encourage 
a settlement under the auspices of the united nations 
thailand recently helped arrange talks in tokyo between prince 
sihanouk and hun sen installed as head of cambodias government 
after the vietnamese invasion in 1978 chatichai also conferred 
recently with xu dunxin a top chinese official who recently 
traveled to both bangkok and vietnam 
the united states has opposed the flow of chinese arms to the 
communist khmer rouge strongest of the warring cambodian factions 
who are blamed for killing more than 1 million of their countrymen 
during their bloody 197578 rule 
some environmental groups were staging a protest march today 
against what they called crass hypocrisy by chatichais 
government in prohibiting logging within thailand while granting 
more than 40 licenses to thai companies to harvest teak and other 
rain forest timber in burma 
