the legislature ordered a twomonth delay thursday 
in an unpopular threefold increase in bread prices a centerpiece 
of mikhail s gorbachevs market reforms 
the supreme soviet voted 31933 that the government should 
produce another version of the plan in september easing the effect 
of price increases bread prices the staple of the soviet diet 
would have increased july 1 
gorbachev had indicated the price increase was a test of the 
soviet unions willingness to tolerate a free market it was 
intended to help pay the cost of recently increased payments to 
grain farmers 
the increase was part of an economic program that touched off 
panic buying in moscow and led the capitals government to require 
proof of residence before allowing purchases 
lawmakers rejected the measure because of its great unpopularity 
among voters said one deputy alexei boiko a member of the 
committee that examined government proposals on economic reform 
the people have been cheated more than once theyre 
mistrustful and they feared they would be cheated again he said 
boiko said delegates from poor regions of central asia where 
consumption of bread is particularly high are really afraid 
theyre worried that this will give rise to real discontent 
he said the decision also was influenced by violent ethnic 
clashes fueled by poverty in central asia in the republic of 
kirghizia 155 people died in ethnic fighting in the past two 
weeks the soviet interior ministry said 
government officials had promised that all 28 billion brought 
in by the price increase would be handed back to consumers through 
compensation programs however officials acknowledged they had not 
fully worked out such programs 
