gorbachev has said that bread is so cheap children sometimes use 
loaves for soccer balls at the same time the country spends its 
scarce foreign currency to buy grain from foreign countries 
one deputy said that because prices paid to grain farmers 
already have been raised keeping bread prices constant would swell 
the government budget deficit 
