the philippine government said it received assurances from the 
us ambassador the british ambassador and the manila 
representative of the un high commissioner on refugees that the 
refugees will be resettled in another country within three years 
the issue has been a sensitive one for the us navy since a 
military jury at subic bay convicted a navy captain of dereliction 
of duty for turning away a boatload of vietnamese in the south 
china sea in june 1988 thirtyone of the vietnamese died and 
survivors turned to cannibalism to stay alive 
there are more than 109000 boat people in camps in southeast 
asian countries including 54541 in hong kong according to un 
and british figures 
britain has classified 10500 of the vietnamese in hong kong as 
genuine political refugees britain wants to send to guam about 
9000 it says are purely seeking a better way of life and have no 
right to asylum 
the rest are awaiting screening and british officials expect 
nearly 90 percent to be classifed as economic migrants 
