schedule said watkins 
the departments waste isolation pilot plant will accept highly 
radioactive waste over a five year test period beginning next year 
he said 
watkins signed a formal record of decision on a supplement 
to the environmental impact statement for the plant certifying 
that the plant meets federal environmental laws 
the department said however further tests would be conducted 
on some environmental issues such as gas generated from metal drums 
and wastes created as a result of corrosion or bacterial action 
the plant will be the countrys first central repository for 
radioactive wastes from nearly a dozen nuclear weapons plants the 
wastes will be placed in salt beds 2150 feet under the ground 
