limits for emissions of zinc solids hexavalent chromium and other 
pollutants she said zinc is dangerous to fish and wildlife and 
hexavalent chromium is dangerous to people and aquatic life 
the privately funded group sued the company in us district 
court in columbus in 1988 seeking the maximum 25000 fine for 
each offense a consent decree is to be filed in federal court 
thursday said steve samuels the groups lawyer 
under the settlement the company will pay 230000 to the ohio 
department of natural resources to reduce acid mine drainage into 
the river 200000 to the nonprofit virginia environmental 
endowment for projects in the martins ferry area 170000 to the 
nonprofit nature conservancy to buy and preserve wetlands on the 
river and 100000 to the us treasury 
wheelingpitt also will put pollution control devices on its 
martins ferry plant and submit monthly reports on its efforts to 
reduce emissions 
