donald dixon rode the texas boom in a few short 
years to the top of an sampl empire that provided him a life of 
luxury and powerful connections in washington his decline was just 
as fast and steep 
since federal regulators forced dixon from the controls of 
vernon savings and loan association in 1986 seven of the thrifts 
former officers and employees have been convicted on bank fraud 
charges 
on thursday dixon himself surrendered to the fbi on 38 counts 
