japanese partners itoyokado co ltd and 7eleven japan co ltd 
for 400 million and the assumption of debt 
under the revised proposal bondholders would receive debt 
securities with an aggregate principal amount of about 550 
million bearing cash interest at rates of 12 percent to 14 percent 
and maturing in six to seven years the original restructuring 
proposal offered bondholders 350 million for their debt 
preferred stockholders would get shares of a new issue of 
preferred stock or common stock of the same value bondholders and 
preferred shareholders also would end up with a total of 185 
percent of southlands common stock 
the thompson family would see its stake in southland reduced to 
65 percent 
