from the 62 percent gain he estimated in december 
in a semiannual report on ad spending coen said the economic 
indicators have not been very good since the fall of 1989 and they 
are the cause of most of the slowdown in ad spending 
he blamed sluggish retail spending and poor retailer profits for 
depressing the local advertising market this year local ad 
revenues are expected to increase just 47 percent this year to 
