contel corp said thursday it is offering early 
retirement to about 900 employees as part of a previously announced 
costcutting program 
the telecommunications company said it was launching the 
retirement program to avoid layoffs while reducing the workforce 
under the plan a retirement window will be created in july 
during which retiring employees will receive three years toward 
their ages and three years toward their service dates in 
determining individual benefits 
the program will be offered to employees 52 and older who have 
at least seven years of service with the company as of dec 30 and 
are in job classifications and locations that may be affected by 
the restructuring of the telephone operations sector 
contel said in april it was starting a twoyear restructuring to 
make the sector more efficient marketfocused and responsive to 
consumers the restructuring is expected to reduce the workforce by 
4 percent and result in up to 25 million in pretax costs 
