<TEXT>
the united auto workers and the nations big 
three automakers will begin contract negotiations in the third week 
of july for about 500000 workers the union said wednesday 
company spokesmen who declined to be identified said tentative 
dates for the beginning of talks were july 18 at general motors 
corp july 19 at ford motor co and july 20 at chrysler corp 
a uaw spokesman who also refused to be identified confirmed 
those dates 
contracts between the union and each of the big three expire 
sept 14 the first time in 11 years the three contracts have had 
common expiration dates 
in canada talks between the three companies and the canadian 
auto workers union are expected to get under way the following 
week those agreements also expire sept 14 
the uaw has set job security as its top priority in the 
negotiations other issues include wages pension improvements 
health care and more responsive management 
the opening of talks is largely ceremonial with dozens of 
people packed into the main negotiating room at each of the us 
automakers headquarters uaw president owen bieber and chief 
negotiators for the companies shake hands across a huge table 
much of the bargaining takes place in subcommittees that focus 
on specific areas of the contracts economic matters usually are 
among the last negotiated 
an hourly worker on an assembly line now makes about 1575 an 
hour 
traditionally as the deadline draws near the uaw selects a 
target company on which to focus efforts and suspends talks at 
the other two terms of an agreement at the target company called 
a pattern contract then are modified slightly and brought to the 
other two 
this year chrysler labor vice president anthony st john has 
hinted that the financially struggling company may break from the 
pattern 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

