<TEXT>
here are brief details about the new york stock 
exchanges plan for afterhours stock trading and an explanation of 
the current system 
the exchange has been presenting the ideas to wall street 
brokerage firms recently exchange chairman john j phelan jr on 
thursday confirmed plans for a fivestep program to phase in 
afterhours trading perhaps leading to 24hour trading by the year 
2000 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the nyse is open from 930 am to 4 pm eastern time stocks 
of us and foreign companies comprise the 1700 listed on the 
exchange 
trades are entered either manually or electronically on the 
exchange floor specialists on the floor make markets for 
individual stocks by matching buyers with sellers and generate 
action in less heavily traded stocks 
brokers who take orders at banks of yellow telephones on the 
floor often trade with other brokers at a stocks post in those 
cases specialists serve as traffic cops making sure the trade is 
properly recorded 
if there is no buyer or seller the specialist records the order 
and awaits a corresponding transaction or the specialist will 
step in and complete the trade in order to keep the market active 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
in the first stage the nyse would hold two 15 to 45minute 
sessions after the market closes in an attempt to recapture some 
trading currently lost to the london stock exchange that activity 
mainly involves program trading and other techniques typically not 
used by small investors 
one session would allow traders to trade stocks at the days 
closing prices and the other would let them disclose their own 
trades both practices could help program traders complete 
transactions such trades now often are completed in london or via 
independent electronic trading services 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
sometime in 1991 the nyse would begin holding auctions of each 
listed stock at 8 pm midnight and 5 am eastern time the 
stocks would trade once at each auction with trades combined at 
one agreedupon price for each issue traded 
brokers could enter electronic orders for stocks at their 
offices in the evening in new york as the trading day begins in 
tokyo they would be able to see what other orders had been placed 
and alter their own 
at 8 pm the exchange would pair off as many orders as 
possible in one huge trade that could involve millions of shares 
and hundreds of buyers and sellers the process would be repeated 
at midnight and 5 am when the london market opens 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the plan calls for moving at some stage to a form of 
conventional trading overnight leading finally to roundtheclock 
trading exchange officials didnt give details about the later 
stages although phelan said 24hour trading could be in place by 
the year 2000 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

